cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper discusses a competition for agents that can play classic text-based adventure games, which involves challenges for natural language understanding and generation. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.CL (computation and language). The paper also presents results of an improved evaluation of the competitors, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (learning) as well. Additionally, the competition framework and competitors are open source, which could place it in cs.CC (computing and communication) or cs.GT (game theory).
